ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Challenging but rewarding. Engaging and thought provoking. At times maddening, but definitely worth the brain exercise.
This is the class where you'll start to get what syntax is all about.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It helped me in about the ways I expected and wanted -- broadening my linguistic knowledge, strengthening my foundation. I don't anticipate doing syntactic research, primarily, but it put new analytical tools in my toolbelt, which is always good.
This course was very helpful for giving me an overview of syntactic theory. For the first time I feel like I have something of a grasp on many of these issues that have been completely opaque to me.
